The paper deals with shape matching using unsupervised deep learning, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The method also involves optimizing for global structural properties, which is related to computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.GR). Finally, the paper presents results on benchmarks involving 3D shapes, which is a topic that falls under multimedia (cs.MM).
